 Academy Awards|1961]]\n|rowspan=3|''[[The Apartment]]''\n|[[Academy Award for Best Picture|Best Picture]]\n|{{won}}\n|rowspan=3 style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/1961|publisher=Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences|accessdate=17 December 2019|title=The 33rd Academy Awards}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Academy Award for Best Director|Best Director]]\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|[[Academy Award for Best Original Screenplay|Best Original Screenplay]]\n|{{won}}{{efn|name=Diamond}}\n|-\n|[[39th Academy Awards|1967]]\n|''[[The Fortune Cookie]]''\n|[[Academy Award for Original Screenplay|Best Original Screenplay]]\n|{{nom}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/1967|publisher=Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences|accessdate=17 December 2019|title=The 39th Academy Awards}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[60th Academy Awards|1988]]\n|\n|[[Irving G. Thalberg Memorial Award]]\n|{{won}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.oscars.org/oscars/ceremonies/1988|publisher=Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences|accessdate=17 December 2019|title=The 60th Academy Awards}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[American Film Institute]]\n|1986\n|\n|[[AFI Life Achievement Award|Life Achievement Award]]\n|{{won}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"Phillips1998\"/>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[Berlin International Film Festival]]\n|[[43rd Berlin International Film Festival|1993]]\n|\n|Honorary Golden Bear\n|{{won}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"Phillips1998\">{{cite book|last=Phillips|first=Gene D.|title=Exiles in Hollywood: Major European Film Directors in America|url=https://archive.org/details/exilesinhollywoo0000phil|url-access=registration|year=1998|publisher=Lehigh University Press|isbn=978-0-934223-49-2|page=[https://archive.org/details/exilesinhollywoo0000phil/page/17 17]}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" rowspan=3|[[British Academy Film Awards]]\n|[[13th British Academy Film Awards|1960]]\n|''[[Some Like It Hot]]''\n|[[BAFTA Award for Best Film|Best Film]]\n|{{nom}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://awards.bafta.org/award/1960/film/film-and-british-film|publisher=British Academy Film Awards|title=Film From Any Source in 1960|accessdate=17 December 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[14th British Academy Film Awards|1961]]\n|''[[The Apartment]]''\n|[[BAFTA Award for Best Film|Best Film]]\n|{{won}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://awards.bafta.org/award/1961/film/film-and-british-film|publisher=British Academy Film Awards|title=Film From Any Source in 1961|accessdate=17 December 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[48th British Academy Film Awards|1995]]\n|\n|[[BAFTA Fellowship]]\n|{{won}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|publisher=British Academy Film Awards|url=http://awards.bafta.org/award/1995/film/|title=Film in 1995|accessdate=17 December 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[Cannes Film Festival]]\n|[[1946 Cannes Film Festival|1946]]\n|''[[The Lost Weekend (film)|The Lost Weekend]]''\n|Best American Film\n|{{won}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/05/13/movies/recalling-the-first-cannes-film-festival-as-a-cold-war-brewed-in-1946.html|title=Recalling the First Cannes Film Festival, as a Cold War Brewed in 1946|date=May 12, 2016|accessdate=December 19, 2019|last=Murphy|first=Mary Jo|work=The New York Times}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" rowspan=10|[[Directors Guild of America Award]]\n|1951\n|''[[Sunset Boulevard (film)|Sunset Boulevard]]''\n|[[Directors Guild of America Award for Outstanding Directing \u2013 Feature Film|Outstanding Directing \u2013 Feature Film]]\n|{{nom}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=10|<ref name=\"Phillips1998\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dga.org/Awards/Explore.aspx|title=Awards / Winner and Nominee Search|publisher=Directors Guild of America|accessdate=December 19, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|1954\n|''[[Stalag 17]]''\n|[[Directors Guild of America Award for Outstanding Directing \u2013 Feature Film|Outstanding Directing \u2013 Feature Film]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|1955\n|''[[Sabrina (1954 film)|Sabrina]]''\n|[[Directors Guild of America Award for Outstanding Directing \u2013 Feature Film|Outstanding Directing \u2013 Feature Film]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|1956\n|''[[The Seven Year Itch]]''\n|[[Directors Guild of America Award for Outstanding Directing \u2013 Feature Film|Outstanding Directing \u2013 Feature Film]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|rowspan=2|1958\n|''[[Love in the Afternoon (1957 film)|Love in the Afternoon]]''\n|[[Directors Guild of America Award for Outstanding Directing \u2013 Feature Film|Outstanding Directing \u2013 Feature Film]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|''[[Witness for the Prosecution (1957 film)|Witness for the Prosecution]]''\n|[[Directors Guild of America Award for Outstanding Directing \u2013 Feature Film|Outstanding Directing \u2013 Feature Film]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|1960\n|''[[Some Like It Hot]]''\n|[[Directors Guild of America Award for Outstanding Directing \u2013 Feature Film|Outstanding Directing \u2013 Feature Film]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n|1961\n|''[[The Apartment]]''\n|[[Directors Guild of America Award for Outstanding Directing \u2013 Feature Film|Outstanding Directing \u2013 Feature Film]]\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|1985\n|\n|[[Directors Guild of America Lifetime Achievement Award \u2013 Feature Film|Lifetime Achievement Award \u2013 Feature Film]]\n|{{won}}\n|-\n|1991\n|\n|Preston Sturges Award\n|{{won}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[Film at Lincoln Center]]\n|1982\n|\n|Gala tribute\n|{{won}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"Phillips1998\"/>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\" rowspan=7|[[Golden Globe Awards]]\n|[[3rd Golden Globe Awards|1946]]\n|''[[The Lost Weekend (film)|The Lost Weekend]]''\n|[[Golden Globe Award for Best Director|Best Director]]\n|{{won}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=GG>{{cite web|url=https://www.goldenglobes.com/person/billy-wilder|title=Billy Wilder|accessdate=17 December 2019|publisher=Hollywood Foreign Press Association}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[8th Golden Globe Awards|1951]]\n|rowspan=2|''[[Sunset Boulevard (film)|Sunset Boulevard]]''\n|[[Golden Globe Award for Best Director|Best Director]]\n|{{won}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=2|<ref name=GG/>\n|-\n|[[Golden Globe Award for Best Screenplay|Best Screenplay]]\n|{{nom}}{{efn|name=Marshman}}\n|-\n|[[15th Golden Globe Awards|1958]]\n|''[[Witness for the Prosecution (1957 film)|Witness for the Prosecution]]''\n|[[Golden Globe Award for Best Director|Best Director]]\n|{{nom}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=GG/>\n|-\n|[[18th Golden Globe Awards|1961]]\n|''[[The Apartment]]''\n|[[Golden Globe Award for Best Director|Best Director]]\n|{{nom}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=GG/>\n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[30th Golden Globe Awards|1973]]\n|rowspan=2|''[[Avanti!]]''\n|[[Golden Globe Award for Best Director|Best Director]]\n|{{nom}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=2|<ref name=GG/>\n|-\n|[[Golden Globe Award for Best Screenplay|Best Screenplay]]\n|{{nom}}{{efn|name=Diamond}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[John F. Kennedy Center for the Performing Arts]]\n|1990\n|\n|[[Kennedy Center Honors]]\n|{{won}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1990/12/03/arts/honors-for-5-at-the-kennedy-center.html|work=The New York Times|date=December 3, 1990|last=Gamarekian|first=Barbara|title=Honors for 5 at the Kennedy Center|accessdate=17 December 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[National Endowment for the Arts]]\n|1993\n|\n|[[List of recipients of the National Medal of Arts|National Medal of Arts]]\n|{{won}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"Phillips2010\">{{cite book|last=Phillips|first=Gene|title=Some Like It Wilder: The Life and Controversial Films of Billy Wilder|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=5uohNoRFkwIC&pg=PT390|date=5 February 2010|publisher=University Press of Kentucky|isbn=0-8131-7367-1|page=390}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|[[Producers Guild of America Awa